          Hold context toolSessions in a Map, by context (webapp) id. TODO: ConcurrentHashMap may be better for multiple writers

          long m_created
          The creation time of the session.

        • m_id

          String m_id
          The session id.

        • m_accessed

          long m_accessed
          Time last accessed (via getSession()).

        • expirationTimeSuggestion

          org.apache.commons.lang.mutable.MutableLong expirationTimeSuggestion
          The possible time this Session may be inactive and available for expiration. This value is an optimization for Terracotta clustered environments, to avoid faulting object in, unless we have a best guess that it may be out of date. We also choose not to use the m_accessed field directly, to avoid updating the SHARED (on every box) data structure, except every inactive/2 period.

        • m_inactiveInterval

          int m_inactiveInterval
          Seconds of inactive time before being automatically invalidated - 0 turns off this feature.

        • m_userId

          String m_userId
          The user id for this session.

        • m_userEid

          String m_userEid
          The user enterprise id for this session.

        • m_valid

          boolean m_valid
          True while the session is valid.
